COMPILE
=======

$ dune build


RUN
====

$ _build/default/coqcryptoline.exe [ ARGS ] FILE


ARGUMENTS
---------

* -jobs N		Set the number of concurrent jobs
* -fork			Use fork instead of lwt if the number of concurrent
			jobs is greater than 1
* -sat_solver		Specify the SAT solver
			(cadical, glucose, or cryptominisat)
* -cadical		Set the path to cadical
			(implies -sat_solver cadical)
* -glucose		Set the path to glucose
			(implies -sat_solver glucose)
* -cryptominisat	Set the path to cryptominisat
			(implies -sat_solver cryptominisat)
* -sat_cert		Specify the SAT certifier (drat, grat, or lrat)
* -drat-trim		Set the path to drat-trim
* -gratchk		Set the path to gratchk
* -gratgen		Set the path to gratgen
* -lrat			Set the path to lrat-checker
* -no_carry_constraint
			Do not add carry constraints
* -singular		Set the path to Singular
* -tmpdir PATH		Specify the directory for storing temporary files
* -v			Print verbose messages


OCAMLRUNPARAM
-------------

It is important to allocate enough space of the minor heap to achieve better
performance. To specify the size of the minor heap, run
_build/default/coqcryptoline.exe with the following prefix:

    OCAMLRUNPARAM=s=X

where X is the size. For example, using the command

    $ OCAMLRUNPARAM=s=2G _build/default/coqcryptoline.exe fe25519_mul.cl

to verify fe25519_mul.cl is much faster than using the command

    $ _build/default/coqcryptoline.exe fe25519_mul.cl


EXAMPLE
-------

$ OCAMLRUNPARAM=s=2G \
        ./_build/default/coqcryptoline.exe -v -jobs 16 \
        -sat_solver cadical -sat_cert grat \
        -no_carry_constraint -tmpdir .
